SENATE BILL 960
F1 6lr1517
CF HB 1430
By: Senator Rosapepe
Introduced and read first time: February 11, 2026
Assigned to: Rules
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Maryland Public Charter School Program – School Facilities – Funding
3 FOR the purpose of requiring the Interagency Commission on School Construction to
4 distribute certain funds to public charter schools for the maintenance and operation
5 of public charter school facilities; and generally relating to the funding of public
6 charter school facilities in the Maryland Public Charter School Program.
7 BY adding to
8 Article – Education
9 Section 9–109(c)
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Education
15 9–109.
16 (C) (1) IN THIS SUBSECTION, “PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL FACILITIES”
17 MEANS PREMISES THAT ARE:
18 (I) OWNED OR LEASED BY A PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL; OR
19 (II) OCCUPIED AND UTILIZED BY A PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL
20 TO PROVIDE A PROGRAM OF PRIMARY OR SECONDARY EDUCATION TO ITS
21 STUDENTS.
22 (2) (I) THE INTERAGENCY COMMISSION ON SCHOOL
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *sb0960*

2 SENATE BILL 960
1 CONSTRUCTION SHALL DISTRIBUTE FUNDS TO PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOLS FOR THE
2 MAINTENANCE AND OPERATION OF PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL FACILITIES.
3 (II) FUNDS DISBURSED UNDER SUBPARAGRAPH (I) OF THIS
4 PARAGRAPH SHALL BE PAID DIRECTLY TO THE PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL AND MAY
5 NOT BE PAID TO A LOCAL GOVERNING BODY OR COUNTY BOARD.
6 (3) FOR FISCAL YEAR 2028 AND EACH FISCAL YEAR THEREAFTER,
7 THE GOVERNOR SHALL INCLUDE IN THE ANNUAL BUDGET BILL AN APPROPRIATION
8 FOR THE MAINTENANCE AND OPERATION OF PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL FACILITIES
9 THAT IS EQUAL TO THE TOTAL AGGREGATE STUDENT ENROLLMENT IN THE
10 MARYLAND PUBLIC CHARTER SCHOOL PROGRAM FOR THE PRIOR FISCAL YEAR
11 MULTIPLIED BY $1,600.
12 (4) THE INTERAGENCY COMMISSION ON SCHOOL CONSTRUCTION
13 SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS TO CARRY OUT THIS SUBSECTION.
14 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
15 1, 2026.

